txt.en: 'The Dead shall not trouble the Living!'
'They are near... prepare yourself!'
Instance: Sister of the Gilrain
'O Gilrain, the ceaseless tears of the wandering star...'
'Swell and flood o'er the Men who bear Isildur's scar...'
'To the haunted mountaintop I banish you, foul shades...'
'Evermore bound within to the oath you twice betrayed!'
'The waters of the Gilrain are far more powerful than you know, oath-breaker!'
'I need not dare. I am the Maiden of the Gilrain!'
'Your cause is a hopeless one, oath-breaker. You will not reach the far banks.'
'The waters of this river answer to none but me!'
'Begone from my lands, all of you!'
'Tell your cursed brethren of what awaits those who dare to cross my waters!'
'You are not welcome among the Living!'
'Wherever I turn, no matter how far I travel, you are always there, [placeholder].'
'Yet, this time, you are powerless.'
'The Ruthless Host will sweep across Lebennin like a tide of fear until we rejoin our Master.'
'Indeed, the waters of this river are strange and have kept you from your fears, but nothing so simple can rout the Dead!'
'And who is this that dares to speak?'
'Hah! What power does water have over the Dead?'
'What... what is this? What have you done?'
'We must move swiftly to stop them! Come, [placeholder]!'
'Curse you, you foul Woman! Curse --'
'Death has found you, [placeholder]!'
'Gondor shall succumb to fear!'
'There is no escape for you!'
'Our Master calls to us!'
'You cannot slay the Dead....'
'Fear is all that shall remain....'
'You should not have stood in our way....'
